gov.usgs.anss.utility

Class LoadResearchCWB

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.utility.LoadResearchCWB

  • public class LoadResearchCWB
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is use for to purposes : generate fetch list entries from day files of origins from VMS, and process fetchlist entries for a given date range. The latter just runs the static fetch() method. The former actually uses this object extensively. *
    Switch   arg        Description *= Item is automatic in GSNStationPanel GUI configurations
 -fetch          This is a fetch invocation, process data for some date range from some cwb
                 If this is omitted, then a fetchlist is generated based on the VMS files.
-h       host    The host address of the CWB to get data from
-p       pppp    *The port to connect to on the CWB.
-b     yyyy-mm-dd The lower end of the data range of fetches to process
 -e    yyyy-mm-dd The upper end of the data range of fetches to process (this day is not processed)
 -resip ip.adr   The address of the research CWB which will get a copy of the data via a MiniSeedServer
 -resport port   The port number of MiniSeedServer for the research CWB which will get a copy
